◆ _IsTargetAcceptable()

bool Creature::_IsTargetAcceptable ( Unit const *  target) const
2568{
2569 ASSERT(target);
2570
2571 // if the target cannot be attacked, the target is not acceptable
2572 if (IsFriendlyTo(target) || !target->isTargetableForAttack(false, this) || (m_vehicle && (IsOnVehicle(target) || m_vehicle->GetBase()->IsOnVehicle(target))))
2573 return false;
2574
2575 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_DIED))
2576 {
2577 // some creatures can detect fake death
2578 if (CanIgnoreFeignDeath() && target->HasUnitFlag2(UNIT_FLAG2_FEIGN_DEATH))
2579 return true;
2580 else
2581 return false;
2582 }
2583
2584 Unit const* targetVictim = target->getAttackerForHelper();
2585
2586 // if I'm already fighting target, or I'm hostile towards the target, the target is acceptable
2587 if (IsEngagedBy(target) || IsHostileTo(target))
2588 return true;
2589
2590 // if the target's victim is friendly, and the target is neutral, the target is acceptable
2591 if (targetVictim && !IsNeutralToAll() && IsFriendlyTo(targetVictim))
2592 return true;
2593
2594 // if the target's victim is not friendly, or the target is friendly, the target is not acceptable
2595 return false;
2596}

◆ CalculateMinMaxDamage()

void Creature::CalculateMinMaxDamage ( WeaponAttackType  attType,
bool  normalized,
bool  addTotalPct,
float &  minDamage,
float &  maxDamage,
uint8  damageIndex 
)
overridevirtual

Implements Unit.

1122{
1123 // creatures only have one damage
1124 if (damageIndex != 0)
1125 {
1126 minDamage = 0.f;
1127 maxDamage = 0.f;
1128 return;
1129 }
1130
1131 UnitMods unitMod;
1132 float variance = 1.0f;
1133 switch (attType)
1134 {
1135 case BASE_ATTACK:
1136 default:
1137 variance = GetCreatureTemplate()->BaseVariance;
1138 unitMod = UNIT_MOD_DAMAGE_MAINHAND;
1139 break;
1140 case OFF_ATTACK:
1141 variance = GetCreatureTemplate()->BaseVariance;
1142 unitMod = UNIT_MOD_DAMAGE_OFFHAND;
1143 break;
1144 case RANGED_ATTACK:
1145 variance = GetCreatureTemplate()->RangeVariance;
1146 unitMod = UNIT_MOD_DAMAGE_RANGED;
1147 break;
1148 }
1149
1150 if (attType == OFF_ATTACK && !HasOffhandWeaponForAttack())
1151 {
1152 minDamage = 0.0f;
1153 maxDamage = 0.0f;
1154 return;
1155 }
1156
1157 float weaponMinDamage = GetWeaponDamageRange(attType, MINDAMAGE);
1158 float weaponMaxDamage = GetWeaponDamageRange(attType, MAXDAMAGE);
1159
1160 // Disarm for creatures
1161 if (HasWeapon(attType) && !HasWeaponForAttack(attType))
1162 {
1163 minDamage *= 0.5f;
1164 maxDamage *= 0.5f;
1165 }
1166
1167 float attackPower = GetTotalAttackPowerValue(attType);
1168 float attackSpeedMulti = GetAPMultiplier(attType, normalized);
1169 float baseValue = GetModifierValue(unitMod, BASE_VALUE) + (attackPower / 14.0f) * variance;
1170 float basePct = GetModifierValue(unitMod, BASE_PCT) * attackSpeedMulti;
1171 float totalValue = GetModifierValue(unitMod, TOTAL_VALUE);
1172 float totalPct = addTotalPct ? GetModifierValue(unitMod, TOTAL_PCT) : 1.0f;
1173 float dmgMultiplier = GetCreatureTemplate()->DamageModifier; // = DamageModifier * _GetDamageMod(rank);
1174
1175 minDamage = ((weaponMinDamage + baseValue) * dmgMultiplier * basePct + totalValue) * totalPct;
1176 maxDamage = ((weaponMaxDamage + baseValue) * dmgMultiplier * basePct + totalValue) * totalPct;
1177
1178 // pussywizard: crashfix (casting negative to uint => min > max => assertion in urand)
1179 if (minDamage < 0.0f || minDamage > 1000000000.0f)
1180 minDamage = 0.0f;
1181 if (maxDamage < 0.0f || maxDamage > 1000000000.0f)
1182 maxDamage = 0.0f;
1183 if (minDamage > maxDamage)
1184 minDamage = maxDamage;
1185}

◆ GetAggroRange()

float Creature::GetAggroRange ( Unit const *  target) const
3323{
3324 // Determines the aggro range for creatures
3325 // Based on data from wowwiki due to lack of 3.3.5a data
3326
3327 float aggroRate = sWorld->getRate(RATE_CREATURE_AGGRO);
3328 if (aggroRate == 0)
3329 return 0.0f;
3330
3331 auto creatureLevel = target->getLevelForTarget(this);
3332 auto playerLevel = getLevelForTarget(target);
3333 int32 levelDiff = int32(creatureLevel) - int32(playerLevel);
3334
3335 // The maximum Aggro Radius is capped at 45 yards (25 level difference)
3336 if (levelDiff < -25)
3337 levelDiff = -25;
3338
3339 // The base aggro radius for mob of same level
3340 auto aggroRadius = GetDetectionRange();
3341 if (aggroRadius < 1)
3342 {
3343 return 0.0f;
3344 }
3345 // Aggro Radius varies with level difference at a rate of roughly 1 yard/level
3346 aggroRadius -= (float)levelDiff;
3347
3348 // detect range auras
3349 aggroRadius += GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DETECT_RANGE);
3350
3351 // detected range auras
3352 aggroRadius += target->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DETECTED_RANGE);
3353
3354 // Just in case, we don't want pets running all over the map
3355 if (aggroRadius > MAX_AGGRO_RADIUS)
3356 aggroRadius = MAX_AGGRO_RADIUS;
3357
3358 // Minimum Aggro Radius for a mob seems to be combat range (5 yards)
3359 // hunter pets seem to ignore minimum aggro radius so we'll default it a little higher
3360 float minRange = IsPet() ? 10.0f : 5.0f;
3361 if (aggroRadius < minRange)
3362 aggroRadius = minRange;
3363
3364 return (aggroRadius * aggroRate);
3365}

◆ GetAttackDistance()

float Creature::GetAttackDistance ( Unit const *  player) const
3528{
3529 float aggroRate = sWorld->getRate(RATE_CREATURE_AGGRO);
3530
3531 if (aggroRate == 0)
3532 return 0.0f;
3533
3534 if (!player)
3535 return 0.0f;
3536
3537 uint32 playerLevel = player->getLevelForTarget(this);
3538 uint32 creatureLevel = getLevelForTarget(player);
3539
3540 int32 levelDiff = static_cast<int32>(playerLevel) - static_cast<int32>(creatureLevel);
3541
3542 // "The maximum Aggro Radius has a cap of 25 levels under. Example: A level 30 char has the same Aggro Radius of a level 5 char on a level 60 mob."
3543 if (levelDiff < -25)
3544 levelDiff = -25;
3545
3546 // "The aggro radius of a mob having the same level as the player is roughly 20 yards"
3547 float retDistance = 20.0f;
3548
3549 // "Aggro Radius varies with level difference at a rate of roughly 1 yard/level"
3550 // radius grow if playlevel < creaturelevel
3551 retDistance -= static_cast<float>(levelDiff);
3552
3553 if (creatureLevel + 5 <= sWorld->getIntConfig(CONFIG_MAX_PLAYER_LEVEL))
3554 {
3555 // detect range auras
3556 retDistance += static_cast<float>( GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DETECT_RANGE));
3557
3558 // detected range auras
3559 retDistance += static_cast<float>( player->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DETECTED_RANGE));
3560 }
3561
3562 // "Minimum Aggro Radius for a mob seems to be combat range (5 yards)"
3563 if (retDistance < 5.0f)
3564 retDistance = 5.0f;
3565
3566 return (retDistance * aggroRate);
3567}

1710 // If only dead instance(s) exist, despawn them and spawn a new (maybe also dead) version
1711 const auto creatureBounds = map->GetCreatureBySpawnIdStore().equal_range(spawnId);
1712 std::vector <Creature*> despawnList;
1713
1714 if (creatureBounds.first != creatureBounds.second)
1715 {
1716 for (auto itr = creatureBounds.first; itr != creatureBounds.second; ++itr)
1717 {
1718 if (itr->second->IsAlive())
1719 {
1720 LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Would have spawned {} but {} already exists", spawnId, creatureBounds.first->second->GetGUID().ToString());
1721 return false;
1722 }
1723 else
1724 {
1725 despawnList.push_back(itr->second);
1726 LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Despawned dead instance of spawn {} ({})", spawnId, itr->second->GetGUID().ToString());
1727 }
1728 }
1729

1731 {
1732 despawnCreature->AddObjectToRemoveList();
1733 }
1734 }
1735 }
1736
1737 CreatureData const* data = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureData(spawnId);
1738 if (!data)
1739 {
1740 LOG_ERROR("sql.sql", "Creature (SpawnId: {}) not found in table `creature`, can't load. ", spawnId);
1741 return false;
1742 }
1743
1744 // xinef: this has to be assigned before Create function, properly loads equipment id from DB
1745 m_creatureData = data;
1746 m_spawnId = spawnId;
1747

1749 uint32 entry = GetRandomId(data->id1, data->id2, data->id3);
1750
1751 if (!Create(map->GenerateLowGuid<HighGuid::Unit>(), map, data->phaseMask, entry, 0, data->posX, data->posY, data->posZ, data->orientation, data))
1752 return false;
1753
1754 //We should set first home position, because then AI calls home movement
1755 SetHomePosition(data->posX, data->posY, data->posZ, data->orientation);
1756

1758
1759 m_respawnDelay = data->spawntimesecs;
1760 m_deathState = DeathState::Alive;
1761
1762 m_respawnTime = GetMap()->GetCreatureRespawnTime(m_spawnId);
1763 if (m_respawnTime) // respawn on Update
1764 {
1765 m_deathState = DeathState::Dead;
1766 if (CanFly())
1767 {
1768 float tz = map->GetHeight(GetPhaseMask(), data->posX, data->posY, data->posZ, true, MAX_FALL_DISTANCE);
1769 if (data->posZ - tz > 0.1f && Acore::IsValidMapCoord(tz))
1770 {
1771 Relocate(data->posX, data->posY, tz);
1772 }
1773 }
1774 }
1775

1777

1782 {
1783 curhealth = uint32(curhealth * _GetHealthMod(GetCreatureTemplate()->rank));
1784 if (curhealth < 1)
1785 curhealth = 1;
1786 }
1787 SetPower(POWER_MANA, data->curmana);
1788 }
1789 else
1790 {
1791 curhealth = GetMaxHealth();
1792 SetPower(POWER_MANA, GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA));
1793 }
1794

1796

1799
1800 if (addToMap && !GetMap()->AddToMap(this))
1801 return false;
1802 return true;
1803}

◆ setDeathState()

void Creature::setDeathState ( DeathState  state,
bool  despawn = false 
)
overridevirtual

A creature can be in 4 different states: Alive, JustDied, Corpse, and JustRespawned. The cycle follows the next order:

  • Alive: The creature is alive and has spawned in the world
  • JustDied: The creature has just died. This is the state just before his body appeared
  • Corpse: The creature has been removed from the world, and this corpse has been spawned
  • JustRespawned: The creature has just respawned. Follow when the corpse disappears and the respawn timer is finished
Parameters
stateSpecify one of 4 states above
despawnDespawn the creature immediately, without waiting for any movement to finish

Reimplemented from Unit.

Reimplemented in Minion, and Pet.

◆ SetReactState()

void Creature::SetReactState ( ReactStates  state)
inline

A creature can have 3 ReactStates : Agressive, Passive, Neutral.

  • Agressive : The creature will attack any non friend units in sight
  • Passive : The creature will not attack anyone
  • Neutral : The creature will attack only if attacked
95{ m_reactState = state; }

829 }
830 }
831
832 if (!IsInEvadeMode() && IsAIEnabled)
833 {
834 // do not allow the AI to be changed during update
835 m_AI_locked = true;
836 i_AI->UpdateAI(diff);
837 m_AI_locked = false;
838 }
839
840 // creature can be dead after UpdateAI call
841 // CORPSE/DEAD state will processed at next tick (in other case death timer will be updated unexpectedly)
842 if (!IsAlive())
843 break;
844
845 m_regenTimer -= diff;
846 if (m_regenTimer <= 0)
847 {
848 if (!IsInEvadeMode())
849 {
850 // regenerate health if not in combat or if polymorphed)
851 if (!IsInCombat() || IsPolymorphed())
852 RegenerateHealth();
853 else if (IsNotReachableAndNeedRegen())
854 {
855 // regenerate health if cannot reach the target and the setting is set to do so.
856 // this allows to disable the health regen of raid bosses if pathfinding has issues for whatever reason
857 if (sWorld->getBoolConfig(CONFIG_REGEN_HP_CANNOT_REACH_TARGET_IN_RAID) || !GetMap()->IsRaid())
858 {
859 RegenerateHealth();
860 LOG_DEBUG("entities.unit", "RegenerateHealth() enabled because Creature cannot reach the target. Detail: {}", GetDebugInfo());
861 }
862 else
863 LOG_DEBUG("entities.unit", "RegenerateHealth() disabled even if the Creature cannot reach the target. Detail: {}", GetDebugInfo());
864 }
865 }
866
867 if (getPowerType() == POWER_ENERGY)
868 Regenerate(POWER_ENERGY);
869 else
870 Regenerate(POWER_MANA);
871
872 m_regenTimer += CREATURE_REGEN_INTERVAL;
873 }
874
875 if (CanNotReachTarget() && !IsInEvadeMode())
876 {
877 m_cannotReachTimer += diff;
878 if (m_cannotReachTimer >= (sWorld->getIntConfig(CONFIG_NPC_EVADE_IF_NOT_REACHABLE) * IN_MILLISECONDS))
879 {
880 Player* cannotReachPlayer = ObjectAccessor::GetPlayer(*this, m_cannotReachTarget);
881 if (cannotReachPlayer && IsEngagedBy(cannotReachPlayer) && IsAIEnabled && AI()->OnTeleportUnreacheablePlayer(cannotReachPlayer))
882 {
883 SetCannotReachTarget();
884 }
885 else if (!GetMap()->IsRaid())
886 {
887 auto EnterEvade = [&]()
888 {
889 if (CreatureAI* ai = AI())
890 {
891 ai->EnterEvadeMode(CreatureAI::EvadeReason::EVADE_REASON_NO_PATH);
892 }
893 };
894
895 if (GetThreatMgr().GetThreatListSize() <= 1)
896 {
897 EnterEvade();
898 }
899 else
900 {
901 if (HostileReference* ref = GetThreatMgr().GetOnlineContainer().getReferenceByTarget(m_cannotReachTarget))
902 {
903 ref->removeReference();
904 SetCannotReachTarget();
905 }
906 else
907 {
908 EnterEvade();
909 }
910 }
911 }
912 }
913 }
914 break;
915 }
916 default:
917 break;
918 }
919
920 if (IsInWorld() && !IsDuringRemoveFromWorld())
921 {
922 // pussywizard:
923 if (GetOwnerGUID().IsPlayer())
924 {
925 if (m_transportCheckTimer <= diff)
926 {
927 m_transportCheckTimer = 1000;
928 Transport* newTransport = GetMap()->GetTransportForPos(GetPhaseMask(), GetPositionX(), GetPositionY(), GetPositionZ(), this);
929 if (newTransport != GetTransport())
930 {
931 if (GetTransport())
932 GetTransport()->RemovePassenger(this, true);
933 if (newTransport)
934 newTransport->AddPassenger(this, true);
935 this->StopMovingOnCurrentPos();
936 //SendMovementFlagUpdate();
937 }
938 }
939 else
940 m_transportCheckTimer -= diff;
941 }
942
943 sScriptMgr->OnCreatureUpdate(this, diff);
944 }
945}
